In 2003, Rose with the help of all the members of The Get Up Kids renovated the old Redhouse Recording studio to create Black Lodge Studios.
Rose held an interest in sound recording in his high school years, which was nurtured by his family.
One year he got a Fostex X-15 recorder for Christmas.
The next year he moved up to a Fostex 250, which he still uses.
After an ownership change, he left Studio 55 and tried freelancing for six months.
A year later, he dropped out from school and became a full-time partner in the studio.
On December 6, 2012, Rose announced he will be no longer making records after the 2013 calendar year.

The Get Up Kids' studio album Guilt Show was the first album to be recorded there, and since then the studio has thrived, having been the studio used for such notable albums as I Am the Movie by Motion City Soundtrack, Killed or Cured by The New Amsterdams, and A Collection of Short Stories by Houston Calls.
The studio also holds several recording workshops during the course of a year, allowing producing hopefuls to earn hands-on experience with real equipment in a real studio setting.
